verbose_text: Consistent with the inhibitory effect of HOXC10-F4 on the interaction of HOXC10 and PRMT5, we also found that overexpression of HOXC10-F4 peptide significantly abrogated HOXC10 induced VEGFA upregulation and reduced the ability of HOXC10 transduced cells to induce tube formation and proliferation of HUVECs, which provided further evidence that HOXC10 activates VEGFA transcription by interacting with PRMT5.
